Plot - Harleen Sahani, a bank receptionist, (Katrina Kaif) finds herself involved with Rajveer Nanda (Hrithik Roshan), a thief who has stolen a diamond known as &quot;The Kohinoor&quot;. What turned out to be a date at a restaurant ends up in Harleen's life been plunged into danger. Authorities and a notorious criminal Omar Zafar (Danny Denzongpa) are after Rajveer.

Rajveer turns Harleen's life around, telling her to do what needs to be done now, while Rajveer's biggest wish is to return home after all is finished. Rajveer sedates Harleen through the film so that he takes her to a safe place because her life is in danger.

It is revealed that Rajveer is actually Jai Nanda. He had a brother Viren Nanda (Jimmy Shergill) who died in the line of duty (it was actually Omar Zafar and Hamid Gul (Javed Jaaferi) who killed him by burning him alive).

The &quot;Kohinoor&quot;, however was never stolen in the first place and it was revealed its theft was all a ruse, because Rajveer/Jai wanted to get closer to Omar and extract revenge. He kills Omar by setting him ablaze in his water-driven airplane. The film ends with Harleen taking Rajveer home.


